  "body": "`Using geth --syncmode fast --http --gcmode archive --datadir /var/lib/geth`\r\n\r\nReached the 12 million block mark rather fast,  but has since stalled in the same region for 3 weeks, and seems to be incrementing by one block every 2-3 seconds. At this rate, I'll be synced in half a year if im lucky.\r\n\r\nDisk usage is currently at just under 1TB\r\n\r\nI am running on an at the moment practically dedicated 24 core 2.40GHz 5gen intel cpu with SSD SATA and 32 G ram.\r\n\r\nIs this really the expected benchmark, or am I doing something wrong? ",
