    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "You are running the archive node by setting the flag `--gcmode archive`. And also you are using fast sync for initial state sync `--syncmode fast` it means you won't have the historical state data until the initial sync is finished. Not sure it's your expected behavior.\r\n\r\nAnd regarding the archive node, it will push a lot of state data into disk and even worse the flushed data will involve the database compaction with almost all stored data in disk. I don't have the latest performance number for archive node, but it's indeed very slow.",
